<span id="v.iv.li-p2"></span><span class="c12"><span
id="v.iv.li-p2.1"></span>Eutropius, <span
id="fr_2657"></span>[2658](#fn_2657.md) </span> the presbyter, wrote to two
sisters, handmaids of Christ, who had been disinherited by their parents
on account of their devotion to chastity and their love for religion,
two *Consolatory letters* in the form of small books, written in
polished and clear language and fortified not only by argument, but also
by testimonies from the Scriptures.

